				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think it makes sense for Verant to want their official boards to focus on the good aspects of the game.  To us this is a game.  To them this is a business.  Of course they want you to enjoy the game - that makes good business sense, but they don't want to help you work to piss off other customers either.<BR>
<BR>
They are not saying you can't complain or ask for changes.  You can complain to them through the developer's board - they'll see it.  What they are saying is that if you want to ***** and grandstand publicly, they don't need to be paying for it. Nor do they need to supply you with a pulpit from which to rant by having it on their page.<BR>
<BR>
Nor is this censorship.  You have the right to complain anywhere you want that you pay for or that allows you to do so on their dime.  Would you print others flames and complaints about yourself on your own web page?  <BR>
<BR>
Fernando 
				</font>
