	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is a reason that Verant gets enraged about being called Nazis-- not only is it an unfair comparison and an incredible misreading of history to call them Nazis, it's also merely an inflamatory comment with no merit to it.<BR>
<BR>
You can't compare what has happened to the boards to the Nazis burning books, no matter how hard you try to rationalize it. The Nazi regime was a government-- Verant is a private company.<BR>
<BR>
Re-read the First Amendment. The first few words are &quot;CONGRESS shall make no law...&quot;. The key word is Congress-- the First Amendment applies ONLY to the government and what it can and cannot regulate. It does not apply to private businesses like Verant. Like it or not, they are within their rights to change the boards as they see fit.<BR>
<BR>
Whineplay was called Whineplay for a reason-- it was mostly filled with pointless whines or melodrama. Not a day went by where every class in some form or fashion wasn't declared dead: &quot;Wizards Dead&quot; &quot;VI just killed [insert class here] AGAIN!&quot;, etc. etc. The boards were worthless when it came to getting real ideas across because they were dominated by incessant whines, flames (like calling VI Nazis-- yes, it's a flame) and drivel.<BR>
<BR>
Suck it up and live with it. This change was brought on by the people that posted there, not by Verant's inability to handle criticism-- they can deal with that. They just didn't want to deal with the immaturity and whining on the boards anymore.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
